cking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I propose the following change:\n\n``` ruby\ndef pretty_format(object)\n  case object\n  when String, Numeric, Symbol, Arbre::Element\n    object.to_s\n  when TrueClass, FalseClass\n    status_tag value\n  when Date, Time\n    localize object, format: active_admin_application.localize_format\n  else\n    if defined?(::ActiveRecord) && object.is_a?(ActiveRecord::Base) ||\n       defined?(::Mongoid)      && object.class.include?(Mongoid::Document)\n      auto_link object\n    else\n      display_name object\n    end\n  end\nend\n```\n\nin [ActiveAdmin::ViewHelpers::DisplayHelper](https://github.com/activeadmin/activeadmin/blob/552289200049851540393db2dbf142ab311ced1e/lib/active_admin/view_helpers/display_helper.rb#L68)\n\nThe idea is that currently the value of boolean columns is displayed via `status_tag` and the result of methods, that return  `true`/`false`, is displayed via a ✔/✗. In an attributes table, where some of the rows are for boolean columns and some of the rows are for methods returning booleans, the table looks inconsistent.\n\nWould such a PR be accepted?\n","closed_by":{"login":"Fivell","id":120269,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDI2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/120269?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell","html_url":"https://github.com/Fivell","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Fivell/received_events","type":"User","u